    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Thickness and parallelism inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "687_5.0_jpn_11581575_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Inspect the sliding surfaces of the brake disc (A) for cracks, abnormal scratches or stepped wear. Measure the thickness of the brake disc at 8 locations at approximately 45° intervals, 10 mm closer to the center from the outer circumference of the disc. The smallest of these measurements shall be the limit value. If the thickness is below the limit, Replace the brake disc. If the parallelism exceeds the limit value, the brake disc should be milled and corrected. Inspect the front brake disc for runout.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000688",
          "label": "Replace the brake disc.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Brake Disc Thickness: 1.0",
            "colspan": 4
          }
        ],
        [
          {
