      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000659",
          "label": "Front wheel removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Brake caliper and bracket removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "687_5.0_jpn_11581581_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the brake hose clamp bolt (A). Remove the caliper (B) from the knuckle and secure the caliper with a wire or similar."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When securing the caliper, be very careful not to damage other parts.",
        "Do not suspend the caliper by the brake hose.",
        "Do not forcefully twist the brake hose."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Cutting correction"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "687_5.0_jpn_11581582_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Cut and correct using a brake disc grinder (specially designated commercial tool) (A). After cutting correction, check the runout and parallelism of the brake disc again to confirm that it is within the following limits."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Cutting correction is performed with a motor-driven brake disc grinder."
        },
        {
          "text": "Cutting correction is performed with a motor-driven brake disc grinder."
        },
        {
          "text": "Refer to the instruction manual of the grinder for the use of the brake disc grinder."
        },
        {
          "text": "Refer to the instruction manual of the grinder for the use of the brake disc grinder."
        },
        {
          "text": "Cut the brake disc so that it does not fall below the thickness limit value."
        },
        {
          "text": "Cut the brake disc so that it does not fall below the thickness limit value."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Limits after cutting modification: 1.",
            "colspan": 3
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": ""
          },
          {
            "text": "Brake disc runout"
          },
          {
            "text": "0.04mm"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Brake disc parallelism: 1"
          },
          {
            "text": "0.015mm"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Brake caliper and bracket installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "687_5.0_jpn_11581583_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install the caliper (A) on the knuckle. Install the brake hose clamp bolt (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not forcefully twist the brake hose."
      ]
    },
